---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms of Use for Open Medical Skills — understand your rights and responsibilities when using this physician-curated medical AI skills directory."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl dark:text-white">
      Terms of Use
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
      Last updated: March 2, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-7">

      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section>
        <p>
          Welcome to <strong>Open Medical Skills</strong>, a project of <strong>IntelMedica.ai</strong>. By accessing
          or using this website, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree with any part of
          these terms, please do not use the site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 1. Acceptance of Terms -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          By accessing, browsing, or using Open Medical Skills, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and
          agree to be bound by these Terms of Use, as well as our Privacy Policy. These terms apply to all visitors,
          users, contributors, and anyone who accesses the site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 2. Description of Service -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is a <strong>curated directory</strong> of medical AI agent skills and plugins. We provide:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>A searchable catalog of medical AI tools</li>
          <li>Physician review and classification of submitted skills</li>
          <li>Installation instructions and links to third-party repositories</li>
          <li>A submission pipeline for contributors to add new skills</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          <strong>We are a directory service only.</strong> We do not develop, host, or maintain the skills and plugins
          listed here. Each listed tool is created and maintained by independent third-party developers, researchers,
          or organizations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 3. Medical Disclaimer -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">3. Medical Disclaimer (Critical — Read Carefully)</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border-2 border-red-200 bg-red-50 p-5 dark:border-red-800/50 dark:bg-red-950/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-red-900 dark:text-red-200">IMPORTANT MEDICAL DISCLAIMER</p>
          <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm text-red-800 dark:text-red-300">
            <p>
              <strong>Open Medical Skills is NOT medical advice.</strong> We are a directory of software tools. We do not
              provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. The skills listed here are:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
              <li><strong>Not FDA-cleared medical devices</strong> (unless explicitly stated)</li>
              <li><strong>Not replacements for clinical judgment</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Not substitutes for physician training or expertise</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Not substitutes for the physician-patient relationship</strong></li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              <strong>Healthcare professionals</strong>: You are solely responsible for evaluating the clinical appropriateness,
              safety, and accuracy of any tool before using it in patient care, research, or clinical workflows. Physician
              review of a listing is a curation effort — it is <strong>not a guarantee of safety, efficacy, or fitness for
              any particular clinical purpose.</strong>
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>Always independently verify medical information and consult appropriate clinical guidelines, specialists,
              and literature before making clinical decisions.</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 4. No Warranty -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">4. No Warranty</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is provided <strong>"AS IS"</strong> and <strong>"AS AVAILABLE"</strong> without warranties
          of any kind, either express or implied, including but not limited to:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Warranties of merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose</li>
          <li>Warranties that the information is accurate, complete, or up to date</li>
          <li>Warranties that the site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or secure</li>
          <li>Warranties regarding the safety, efficacy, or appropriateness of listed skills</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          <strong>Third-party skills</strong>: Each skill or plugin is developed and maintained by independent third parties.
          IntelMedica.ai does not control, endorse, or guarantee the quality, safety, or functionality of any listed tool.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 5. Limitation of Liability -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, <strong>IntelMedica.ai, its founders, employees, contractors, and
          physician reviewers SHALL NOT BE LIABLE</strong> for any:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages</li>
          <li>Loss of profits, revenue, data, or goodwill</li>
          <li>Patient harm, medical errors, or adverse clinical outcomes</li>
          <li>Damages arising from the use of any skill or plugin listed on this site</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          This limitation applies <strong>whether or not we have been advised of the possibility of such damages</strong>,
          and regardless of the legal theory (contract, tort, negligence, strict liability, or otherwise).
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion or limitation of certain warranties or liabilities. In such
          jurisdictions, our liability will be limited to the maximum extent permitted by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 6. User Responsibilities -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">6. User Responsibilities</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          By using Open Medical Skills, you agree to:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Independently verify all tools</strong> before deploying them in clinical, research, or production
            environments. Do not rely solely on our physician review.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Comply with applicable laws</strong>, including HIPAA, GDPR, FDA regulations, and local medical
            practice laws.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Review each skill's license, privacy policy, and documentation</strong> before installation.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Use skills only within your scope of training and licensure.</strong> Do not use tools for purposes
            beyond your clinical expertise.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Not misuse the site</strong> — e.g., no spamming, scraping, malicious submissions, or attempts to
            compromise security.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- 7. Submission Terms -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">7. Submission and Contribution Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you submit a skill, plugin, or other contribution to Open Medical Skills (via GitHub pull request, web form,
          or otherwise), you agree that:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Your submission becomes part of the open-source project.</strong> Submissions are publicly visible
            and will be licensed under the project's open-source license (to be specified in the repository).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>You have the right to submit the content.</strong> You represent that you own or have permission
            to share the content you submit.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Physician review is discretionary.</strong> We reserve the right to accept, reject, or remove any
            submission at our sole discretion, without explanation.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>You retain ownership of your work.</strong> Submitting a skill to the directory does not transfer
            ownership of the underlying code or intellectual property to IntelMedica.ai.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- 8. Intellectual Property -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">8. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The <strong>Open Medical Skills directory and website</strong> (design, layout, documentation, review process)
          are open source and licensed under [TBD — to be specified in repository].
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Each <strong>listed skill or plugin</strong> is owned by its respective author and is subject to its own license.
          We do not claim ownership of third-party skills.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The <strong>IntelMedica.ai name and branding</strong> are proprietary to IntelMedica.ai and may not be used
          without permission.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 9. Physician Review Disclaimer -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">9. Physician Review Is Best-Effort</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Skills listed on Open Medical Skills are reviewed by physician maintainers to assess clinical appropriateness,
          safety classification, and evidence level. However:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Physician review is not a guarantee.</strong> It does not certify safety, efficacy, or regulatory compliance.</li>
          <li><strong>Review is subjective.</strong> Different physicians may have different clinical opinions.</li>
          <li><strong>Skills change over time.</strong> A tool may be updated by its author after review. We do not guarantee ongoing monitoring.</li>
          <li><strong>No liability for review errors.</strong> Physician reviewers are not liable for errors, omissions, or changes to skills post-review.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- 10. Termination and Removal -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">10. Termination and Removal of Listings</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We reserve the right to:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Remove any skill or plugin from the directory at any time, for any reason</li>
          <li>Terminate or restrict access to the site for users who violate these terms</li>
          <li>Modify, suspend, or discontinue the site or any part of it without notice</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- 11. Governing Law -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">11. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          These Terms of Use shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <strong>[Jurisdiction TBD]</strong>,
          without regard to its conflict of law provisions. Any disputes arising from these terms or your use of the site
          shall be resolved in the courts of [Jurisdiction TBD].
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 12. Changes to Terms -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">12. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We may update these Terms of Use from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, legal requirements, or
          the scope of our service. Changes will be posted on this page with a new "Last updated" date.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          <strong>Changes are effective immediately upon posting.</strong> Your continued use of the site after changes
          are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated terms. If you do not agree with the new terms, you must stop
          using the site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 13. Severability -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">13. Severability</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If any provision of these Terms of Use is found to be invalid or unenforceable by a court of competent jurisdiction,
          the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 14. Entire Agreement -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">14. Entire Agreement</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          These Terms of Use, together with our Privacy Policy, constitute the entire agreement between you and
          IntelMedica.ai regarding your use of Open Medical Skills. They supersede any prior agreements or understandings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 15. Contact -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">15. Contact Information</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you have questions about these Terms of Use, please contact:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900/50">
          <p class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">IntelMedica.ai</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm">Email: <a href="mailto:legal@intelmedica.ai" class="text-primary hover:underline">legal@intelmedica.ai</a></p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">
            (Contact details will be updated with full mailing address and phone number when available)
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Footer Note -->
      <section class="mt-12 border-t border-slate-200 pt-8 dark:border-slate-800">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500">
          <strong>Open Medical Skills</strong> is a project of <strong>IntelMedica.ai</strong>, founded by a physician.
          Our mission is to curate and maintain a trusted directory of medical AI tools that serve the healthcare community
          safely and transparently.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
